refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public boolAMQPConnection::setTimeout inttimeout
Set the amount of time, in seconds, after which a call to the server will timeout. This value can be a float, so a 500ms timeout would results in a timeout value of 0.5. A call to this method will override the default value set by the amqp.timeout INI setting.

&reftitle.parameters;




   timeout



     The timeout the AMQPConnection object will enforce when interacting with the broker.

  &reftitle.examples;



    AMQPConnection::setTimeout example


<?php

/* Create a new connection */
$cnn = new AMQPConnection();

// set the timeout
$cnn->setTimeout(0.5);

?>
